<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: On the Druid</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?The RealmWeaver">The RealmWeaver</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:59 p.m. 15/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: On the Druid<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1451" TARGET=_self>Re: On the Druid</A> (Tarquin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>&gt; HEAL
<BR>&gt; OFFENSE
<BR>&gt; MEDIOCRE MELEE
<BR>&gt; BUFFS
<BR>&gt; DEBUFFS
<BR>&gt; LEVITATE
<BR>&gt; INVIS
<BR>&gt; ROOT
<BR>&gt; +
<P>&gt; I mean god, they got best features
<P>&gt; no other class has all of this.
<P>Your point is taken, but your not looking deep enough into the issue. Healing: Yes they get it, but not nearly as powerful as clerics or probably even Paladins. Offense: Yes they get it, but not nearly as powerful as Wizards, Magicians, or probably even Enchanters. Mediocre Melle: EXACTLY - Mediocre, not nearly as good as rangers, warriors, monks, shamans, or probably even rogues. Buffs and Debuffs: Yes, but do they compare to enchanters? Do they compare to Necromancers - no. Levitate: They are travelers, it is their job to travel lightly and quickly. Invis: Again, travelers. Root: They command nature, this is their most valued skill.
<P>In short, yes, they get many different skills, but not nearly at the level as other classes. They are a special class in and of themselves with respect to nature, but they combine the usefullness of many other classes. As their player-guide says, they are a "jack of all trades" but a master of none, they can do a lot of things, but few things as well as other, more specialized classes.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
